-- Nigerian Agency Says 29 Survivors Found After Boat Sinking
-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 2013-03-21T14:20:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-21/nigerian-agency-says-29-survivors-found-after-boat-sinking.html
At least 29 people have been
rescued after a boat capsized about 40 nautical miles off the
coast of southeastern  Nigeria  on March 15, the National
Emergency Management Agency said.  Nine bodies were recovered after the wooden boat carrying
about 128 people to Gabon capsized, Yushau Shuaib, a spokesman
for the emergency agency, also known as Nema, said by phone
today from Abuja, the capital.  The emergency agency is continuing with rescue efforts, he
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
